pageContext.claim: “You know he always gets up today, COVID-19, COVID-19. I said Joe, look. We got a country, and I agree with that, and we've done a hell of a job. We've done a hell of a job. If you look at some of our numbers.”
pageContext.analysis: With the death toll over 200,000, far more than than hat Trump in March had said would be a "very good job," it's hard to say that he's done "a hell of a job."
